==English==

===Etymology===
Probably derived from the previous term "horseshedding," meaning to take a person privately (such as to a horse shed or woodshed, separate buildings away from the house) for private cajoling or reprimand.<ref name="SafireWoodshed">{{cite news |last1=Safire |first1=William |authorlink1=[[w|William Safire]] |title=''On Language'' By William Safire: Woodshed Blues |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1981/12/13/magazine/on-language-by-william-safire-woodshed-blues-kimble-mead.html |accessdate=8 November 2020 |work=[[w|The New York Times]] |date=December 13, 1981 |page=16}}</ref>

